title: Shares of several communications and media companies are trading higher as equities gain amid a report suggesting Gilead Sciences' Remdesivir drug showed some effectiveness in treating the coronavirus. This has raised hopes of a sooner return to spending, economic activity, and investment.

Shares of several communications and media companies are trading higher amid overall market strength on optimistic coronavirus outlook. Companies with streaming services had potentially benefited from theater closures.
